INTEGRATION NOTES:

1. Import: Add `from keyboard_chat import KeyboardChat` at the top of face_display.py.

2. Init: In main(), after pygame.init(), create the chat instance:
       chat = KeyboardChat()
       chat.load_env("/home/user/cypherclaw/.env")

3. Event routing: In the pygame event loop, route keyboard events:
       if event.type == pygame.KEYDOWN:
           if event.key == pygame.K_TAB and not chat.active:
               chat.toggle()  # Tab opens chat
           elif chat.active:
               chat.handle_keypress(event.key, event.unicode, event.mod)
               # Tab and Escape close chat (handled inside handle_keypress)

   NOTE: When chat.active is True, ALL keypresses go to the chat.
   When chat.active is False, only Tab opens it. This prevents the chat
   from swallowing keypresses meant for other face_display controls.

4. Polling + rendering: Each frame, after building the PIL image:
       if chat.active:
           chat.poll_incoming()
       chat.render_overlay(img)  # no-op when inactive

   This must happen BEFORE converting the PIL image to a pygame surface:
       surface = pygame.image.fromstring(img.tobytes(), img.size, img.mode)

5. The img MUST be RGBA mode for the semi-transparent overlay to work.
   If your face currently renders in RGB, convert before overlay:
       img = img.convert("RGBA")

6. KEYBOARD FOCUS: The pygame window MUST have keyboard focus for events
   to arrive. In Openbox, add a startup rule to focus the face window:
       xdotool search --name "CypherClaw Face" windowactivate

   Or in the face_display startup script:
       sleep 2 && xdotool search --name "CypherClaw" windowfocus &

7. VISUAL DESIGN: The overlay uses:
   - Bottom 30% of screen (not 45%) — keeps most of the face visible
   - Alpha 100 (not 180) — see-through, face still visible underneath
   - 30px gradient fade at the top edge — no hard line
   - Auto-fades after 20s of no keypress activity

8. OPENBOX TASKBAR REMOVAL: To hide the taskbar on the face display,
   add to ~/.config/openbox/rc.xml inside <applications>:
       <application class="*">
           <decor>no</decor>
       </application>
   Then: openbox --reconfigure
